ENTRY       EC 4.2.3.83                 Enzyme
NAME        beta-santalene synthase
CLASS       Lyases;
            Carbon-oxygen lyases;
            Acting on phosphates
SYSNAME     (2E,6E)-farnesyl diphosphate lyase (cyclizing, (-)-beta-santalene-forming)
REACTION    (2E,6E)-farnesyl diphosphate = (-)-beta-santalene + diphosphate
SUBSTRATE   (2E,6E)-farnesyl diphosphate [CPD:C00448]
PRODUCT     (-)-beta-santalene;
            diphosphate [CPD:C00013]
COMMENT     The enzyme synthesizes a mixture of sesquiterpenoids from (2E,6E)-farnesyl diphosphate. As well as (-)-beta-santalene (+)-alpha-santalene and (-)-exo-alpha-bergamotene are formed with traces of (+)-epi-beta-santalene. See EC 4.2.3.82 [(+)-alpha-santalene synthase], and EC 4.2.3.81 [(-)-exo-alpha-bergamotene synthase].
HISTORY     EC 4.2.3.83 created 2011
REFERENCE   1  [PMID:21454632]
  AUTHORS   Jones CG, Moniodis J, Zulak KG, Scaffidi A, Plummer JA, Ghisalberti EL, Barbour EL, Bohlmann J
  TITLE     Sandalwood fragrance biosynthesis involves sesquiterpene synthases of both the terpene synthase (TPS)-a and TPS-b subfamilies, including santalene synthases.
  JOURNAL   J. Biol. Chem. 286 (2011) 17445-54.
  ORGANISM  Santalum album
  SEQUENCE  [up:E3W202 E3W203 E3W204]
